SIMPLE: slovenly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slovenly
<hw>Slov"en*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the habits of
a sloven; negligent of neatness and order, especially in
dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>slovenly</qex>, lazy fellow, lolling at his ease.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characteristic of a sloven; lacking neatness and
order; evincing negligence; <as>as, <ex>slovenly</ex>
dress</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slovenly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slovenly
<hw>Slov"en*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>a slovenly manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slovenness</ent>⟦br⟧
